<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-06T08:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-06T08:25:00-05:00" n="785" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/2937: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-06T16:00:00+02:35">December 6, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received December 6—2:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>209. Dessie was bombed this morning between 8 and 9 o’clock by
                                    about 10 Italian planes. American Seventh Day Adventists
                                    Hospital marked with Red Cross said to have been struck but no
                                    one hurt although two rooms said to have been destroyed. No
                                    foreigners reported killed or wounded, but about 25 natives.
                                    Reports so far conflicting. Shall report further as soon as I
                                    receive reliable news.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>